column2: If comma, same pin has multiple connections
If forward slash, it has multiple connections based on jumpers
If yellow, different from Rev D
If blue, pin does not connect vertically to Max32
If blank, it hasn't been checked or is not connected

column6: SB2 is not connected to an interrupt pin
SA1 has to go to INT1 to get it on an interrupt pin
SA2 has to go to INT2 to get it on an interrupt pin
So, you can only use one pin of each encoder through the vertical stack
You can manually connect the encoder signals using J8 and J9
